The paper deals with algorithms for matching and vertex cover on graphs, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and algorithms. The use of coresets and EDCS is a technique that is commonly used in the design of algorithms for massive graphs, which suggests that the paper could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions the use of parallel and distributed algorithms, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
